ingly enhanced as a function of angular distance from the jet axis,\nreaching a maximum at $r=0.6$. Charged particles with transverse momenta above\n4 GeV have an enhanced yield in Pb+Pb collisions in the jet core for angular\ndistances up to $r = 0.05$ from the jet axis, with a suppression at larger\ndistances.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Aug 2019 17:41:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 25 Aug 2020 13:29:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-26"}
